<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Polyphagous. This genus has been found associated with herbaceous plants, shrubs and trees belonging to several plant families (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
